  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention of Health Epidemics in Kaialhu Kono and Pujehun District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">oThe target population will be equipped with the requisite information and knowledge to protect and prevent themselves against infectious diseases.
oAn estimated 80% of the adult target population will have sufficient knowledge in the prevention of Ebola, Lassa fever, and cholera; and will be in a position to inform the responsible local authorities in the case of corresponding danger. 
oTarget population have alternative sources of protein and have their hygiene and sanitation improved to contribute to their improved  health status</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;Establish information, control and response mechanisms to prevent transmission of infectious diseases such as Ebola, Lassa Fever and Cholera,
&#x2022; Initiate early response by local authorities
&#x2022; Organize awareness campaigns towards disease prevention,
&#x2022; Develop early warning systems to timely curb the early spread of contagious infectious diseases through simulations.
&#x2022;Conduct PVCA in 9 PHUs and their catchment villages  in Kono and Kaialhun
Support the development of action plans in Kono and Kailahun district
Support the implementation of action plans in 22 communities</narrative>
  </description>
